This paper deals with optimization algorithms for minimizing stochastic objectives, which is a common problem in machine learning and optimization. The paper proposes new algorithms for both convex and nonconvex objectives, which are important topics in the field of machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves information theory (cs.IT) and control systems (cs.SY) in its analysis, which are less likely but still relevant sub-categories.
